1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,680
(Episode 104)

2
00:00:04,410 --> 00:00:06,410
I'm so sorry.

3
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:08,580
Please, don't worry about her.

4
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:11,080
She's just someone who helps
take care of Father.

5
00:00:11,450 --> 00:00:13,280
I don't consider her my mother-in-law.

6
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:16,450
To me, the late Lee Seong Sil...

7
00:00:16,860 --> 00:00:21,060
is my one and only mother-in-law.

8
00:00:21,530 --> 00:00:25,260
Dae Chang even told you my sister's name?

9
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,800
Of course.

10
00:00:27,770 --> 00:00:30,000
After my mother-in-law passed away,

11
00:00:30,370 --> 00:00:33,140
Father never once remarried.

12
00:00:34,210 --> 00:00:38,140
Now that he's getting on in years,
he needs someone to help take care of him,

13
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:40,010
so she's more like a personal assistant.

14
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:44,280
That woman isn't involved with our family,
so please pay her no mind.

15
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:46,320
I suppose so.

16
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:48,590
It has been a long time.

17
00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:50,960
If he'd found someone nice,

18
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:53,220
I suppose he could have remarried.

19
00:00:54,660 --> 00:00:56,590
Please, you don't have to be
so formal with me.

20
00:00:57,230 --> 00:00:59,100
We're family, after all.

21
00:01:00,830 --> 00:01:01,830
You're right.

22
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:06,500
My brother-in-law is lucky
he has such a sharp daughter-in-law.

23
00:01:08,570 --> 00:01:10,910
Actually, Father has been so down lately,

24
00:01:11,180 --> 00:01:14,380
looking at old photos
of his late wife and daughter.

25
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:16,510
I was getting so worried about him.

26
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:19,150
So this is such wonderful news.

27
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:22,320
- To think my sister-in-law is alive.
- Tell me about it.

28
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:26,320
When that housekeeper told me
that Eun Hye was alive,

29
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:28,730
I flew straight here from the US.

30
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:33,030
- I had to tell Dae Chang.
- Oh, my goodness!

31
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:38,270
For Father, what could be more joyous
than his child returning from the dead?

32
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:42,870
It was so long ago, though.
I'm looking high and low,

33
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:45,480
but I'm worried we won't be able
to find her.

34
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:50,380
So you're searching for her
without any leads?

35
00:01:53,150 --> 00:01:54,950
Jang Mi's foot has a boo-boo.

36
00:01:55,690 --> 00:01:57,290
Jang Mi hurt her foot.

37
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:00,630
Mom, I'm okay now.

38
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:06,230
Jang Mi is pretty. Suk Hee was worried.

39
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,830
You were really worried about me,
weren't you?

40
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:11,740
But look, I'm back, safe and sound.

41
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:14,810
Wait.

42
00:02:15,270 --> 00:02:18,510
What's this on your neck, Mom?
I've never seen this necklace before.

43
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:23,150
That's Grandma's necklace.
She got it from Grandfather's box.

44
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:25,480
That's right.

45
00:02:26,050 --> 00:02:29,750
Dad carefully took it out and polished it.

46
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:33,960
He said it was yours
and put it in a box to keep it safe.

47
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:36,390
This is Suk Hee's.

48
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,960
Yes, it's yours, Mom.

49
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,330
Dad was keeping it safe for you.

50
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:47,870
To think my sister-in-law, presumed dead,
is alive.

51
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,640
I'm shocked and thrilled.

52
00:02:51,010 --> 00:02:53,780
I can't imagine
how you and Father must feel.

53
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:56,510
But...

54
00:02:57,050 --> 00:03:00,520
- How old was she when...
- It was at her 100-day celebration.

55
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:06,720
Dae Chang's construction company
went bankrupt,

56
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:11,460
so he was on the run from creditors
back then.

57
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:15,730
So, my sister had to give birth
to Eun Hye all alone.

58
00:03:16,170 --> 00:03:17,470
So her name is Eun Hye.

59
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,640
Ma Eun Hye.

60
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:23,840
Your sister must have suffered so much.

61
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:25,140
She did.

62
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,450
That's just how business is sometimes.

63
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:32,880
On Eun Hye's 100th day, Dae Chang,
who was on the run, came home.

64
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:35,150
They took a family picture,

65
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:39,160
and he was overjoyed to hold Eun Hye
for the first time.

66
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:43,430
But that's when the creditors stormed in
and had him arrested.

67
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,930
I see.

68
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:48,270
But your sister was there,

69
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:50,570
so how did the baby...

70
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:54,710
My sister was desperately looking for ways
to raise money,

71
00:03:55,570 --> 00:03:57,840
so she decided to come to me in the US.

72
00:03:58,110 --> 00:04:01,680
I was running a small business
in the US at the time.

73
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:04,950
But Eun Hye suddenly came down
with a raging fever,

74
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,190
so my sister couldn't take her
on the plane.

75
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:11,890
My sister planned to fly back to Korea
after getting the money,

76
00:04:12,390 --> 00:04:14,330
so she left the baby
with that witch of a housekeeper.

77
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,730
Oh my gosh. So the housekeeper
ran off with her?

78
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:21,970
She sold her to a broker.
She's a darn witch.

79
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:26,440
The broker was being chased by the police,
fell in the water, and the baby died too.

80
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,410
That's how the whole tragedy unfolded.

81
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,010
We had no idea at the time.

82
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:33,040
We were too busy
looking for that housekeeper.

83
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,410
We had the baby cremated,

84
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:38,050
but later found out
that the baby was Eun Hye,

85
00:04:38,350 --> 00:04:40,920
and my sister collapsed from the shock
and became bedridden.

86
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,920
And in the end...

87
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,990
So back then,

88
00:04:45,460 --> 00:04:48,390
you must have thought
the baby had drowned all this time.

89
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:50,360
My goodness.

90
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,870
If the Chairman's daughter is alive,

91
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,200
what's going to happen to us, Mom?

92
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:01,770
We'll be left with nothing.
We're treated like we're invisible.

93
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:05,480
If his real daughter shows up,
he'll give all his assets to her...

94
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:07,210
and obviously just dote on her, right?

95
00:05:07,610 --> 00:05:10,520
Then we absolutely can't let him find her.

96
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,580
Exactly. You're right.

97
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:17,960
We must find her before the Chairman
and get her out of the picture.

98
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:20,760
Otherwise, we'll be left
with less than nothing!

99
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:24,260
Why do things keep getting
more and more complicated?

100
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,230
Jun Ho kidnapped Oh Jang Mi,

101
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:28,530
but it doesn't look like
he got anything out of it.

102
00:05:29,230 --> 00:05:31,640
And now Baek Ho probably hates me
even more.

103
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:37,580
Jun Ho.

104
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:44,880
Where on earth have you been?

105
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:47,420
How could you do such a thing?

106
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:49,690
Hey, stop it.
Jun Ho is going through enough.

107
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:52,060
Why did you go looking
for trouble then, Jun Ho?

108
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,190
How could you...

109
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:56,890
kidnap your own brother's bride
on his wedding day?

110
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,700
It wasn't a real wedding.

111
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,900
It was just a vow ceremony,
like they were playing house.

112
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,200
That's no excuse.

113
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:08,140
Are you that in love with Oh Jang Mi?

114
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:11,740
She's your brother's woman,
but you'd act so recklessly...

115
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:14,510
and ruin your own future for her?

116
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:16,350
Answer me, Jun Ho.

117
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:19,950
He wouldn't have resorted to kidnapping
if his feelings weren't serious.

118
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,790
But why would you do
something so reckless?

119
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:26,490
That was crossing the line, son.

120
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:28,260
You're right. My feelings are serious.

121
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:32,330
It's the same way you love
CEO Chae Hwa Young, Father.

122
00:06:35,230 --> 00:06:37,070
- Is that so?
- Stop it.

123
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:38,700
How dare you say that in front of me?

124
00:06:40,870 --> 00:06:41,870
Go get some rest.

125
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:43,880
And...

126
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:47,680
don't even think about doing something
so reckless again.

127
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:05,130
To be honest, I was terrified
that I would never see you again, Jang Mi.

128
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,500
And what made me even angrier...

129
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:10,500
was feeling as though
I'd failed to protect you.

130
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,370
I was furious with myself.

131
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:16,540
I just kept believing
this ring would protect me.

132
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,780
Thank you, Jang Mi.

133
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:22,880
Seeing me with Jun Ho this morning
must have made you anxious, right?

134
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:26,480
I hate that I only seem to show you
my worst side.

135
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:30,220
Jang Mi, we're married now.

136
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:32,360
Being married means loving each other,
flaws and all.

137
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,490
Baek Ho.

138
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:53,310
Baek Ho and Jang Mi were about to kiss!

139
00:07:53,410 --> 00:07:56,010
- You scared us!
- Oh my goodness...

140
00:07:56,210 --> 00:07:59,580
Hey, Mom, they're a married couple.

141
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:02,290
It's normal for married couples to kiss,

142
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:03,450
so if they're being all lovey-dovey,

143
00:08:03,450 --> 00:08:05,460
let's just pretend
we don't see them, okay?

144
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:08,890
Fine, I get it.
Be as lovey-dovey as you want.

145
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,600
Let's give them some space.

146
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:13,870
Enjoy yourselves.

147
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:17,740
Hold on.

148
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:20,000
Yes, Grandfather.

149
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:21,540
Jang Mi.

150
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:25,840
Even wringing that punk Kang Jun Ho's neck
wouldn't be enough,

151
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:28,410
so why do you want
to let him off the hook?

152
00:08:28,580 --> 00:08:30,080
The nerve of him!

153
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:32,920
How dare he kidnap a member of my family?

154
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:36,020
Lawyer Kang, turn him over
to the police right now...

155
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,490
- and make him pay for his crime.
- Please don't, Grandfather.

156
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,560
It wasn't a kidnapping.

157
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:46,260
I was the one who pretended
to be Ma Seo Rin...

158
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:49,470
and was about to marry Jun Ho.
It's all my fault.

159
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,500
From Jun Ho's perspective,
he never got a proper explanation.

160
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:56,310
Then, I suddenly told him
that I'd marry Baek Ho.

161
00:08:56,310 --> 00:08:57,810
He must have been very confused.

162
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,480
I...

163
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:02,750
needed time to apologize to him.

164
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:07,080
So you're telling me
he didn't drag you away by force?

165
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:12,020
I just needed some time
to clear my conscience.

166
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:20,260
Grandfather.

167
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,130
And Baek Ho.

168
00:09:22,730 --> 00:09:23,900
I have a favor to ask.

169
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:29,470
I need time to make CEO Chae pay
and sort out this messed-up family tree.

170
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:31,780
After everything is sorted out,

171
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:35,710
I want us to have a real wedding
with everyone gathered to celebrate us.

172
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:39,380
I understand.
If that's what you want, Jang Mi,

173
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:42,450
- I'll wait for you.
- You're right.

174
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:46,760
We can't have a celebration before
Chae Hwa Young pays for what she's done.

175
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:56,200
You, come here.

176
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,370
We need to talk.

177
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:01,440
Ma Seo Rin,
what do you think you're doing?

178
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,540
Let go of her right now.

179
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:05,310
It's all right, Baek Ho.
I'm just going to talk with Seo Rin.

180
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,540
Just wait here for a minute.

181
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:17,320
I never should have met you.

182
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:21,830
Since I met you, you walking disaster,
my life has hit rock bottom!

183
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:23,560
Seo Rin, calm down.

184
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:28,370
If Chae Hwa Young hadn't stolen you away,
we'd be so much happier right now.

185
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:29,430
Happy?

186
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:33,500
Living all chummy
in a hole-in-the-wall shop, playing house?

187
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:37,070
You call that happiness?
I said I'd never live that pathetic life.

188
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:40,710
Rather than live in that house,
crawling with people,

189
00:10:40,710 --> 00:10:42,480
with our dimwit mother, Jung Suk Hee,
and even Oh Bok Gil's stepchildren,

190
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,620
I'd rather live as a monster.

191
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:46,750
Ma Seo Rin!

192
00:10:48,350 --> 00:10:49,350
Oh Jang Mi.

193
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:53,660
- Did you just hit me?
- Yes, I did.

194
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:56,930
I was genuinely happy to see you again.

195
00:10:57,290 --> 00:11:00,000
I was so happy to finally meet Tok Hee
Mom always talked about...

196
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,330
and to meet my other half.

197
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:07,040
But you dragged Chae Hwa Young back here
and called her your mother,

198
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:08,470
and do you have any idea
how heartbroken I was?

199
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:11,010
If you had just stayed away from my man,
Kang Jun Ho,

200
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,280
- I wouldn't have stooped this low.
- Seo Rin.

201
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,850
You took everything from me!

202
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:18,150
My name, my place,

203
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,980
and even Jun Ho.

204
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:23,750
After all that, how dare you slap me?
Who do you think you are?

205
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:27,320
I told you, I had no choice.
Chae Hwa Young was blackmailing me.

206
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:29,060
No.

207
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,060
Have you ever been in my shoes?

208
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,800
It feels like I don't exist
anywhere anymore.

209
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:38,440
I feel like I've suddenly
become invisible.

210
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,970
No one looks for me anymore.

211
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:44,340
Everyone is just looking for you,
my other half.

212
00:11:45,210 --> 00:11:47,280
So where does that leave me?

213
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:50,780
- Where does that leave me?
- Seo Rin.

214
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:54,020
You're still the radiant Seo Rin.

215
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,720
I'm sorry.

216
00:11:58,290 --> 00:11:59,390
I'm so sorry.

217
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:24,620
What do I do?

218
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:27,080
My poor Seo Rin...

219
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:29,450
is so deeply hurt.

220
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:31,190
What can I do...

221
00:12:31,690 --> 00:12:34,090
to make her feel better?

222
00:12:36,590 --> 00:12:38,500
Things will get better with time.

223
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:41,330
I know this must be a difficult time
for Seo Rin,

224
00:12:41,930 --> 00:12:43,300
but this too shall pass.

225
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:46,140
Don't push yourself too hard.

226
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:47,710
Do you really think...

227
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:50,340
time will fix this?

228
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:05,990
Honey.

229
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:09,460
Why would you hide the fact
that your daughter is alive from me?

230
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:14,060
- I'm so hurt.
- Where did you hear that?

231
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:15,600
Your sister-in-law told me.

232
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:18,940
That your daughter, Eun Hye or whatever,
is alive.

233
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:22,170
Grandfather, is it true...

234
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:23,910
that my aunt is really alive?

235
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,410
Yes.

236
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:29,780
All this time, I thought she was dead,

237
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,620
but apparently, she's alive.

238
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:36,050
That's wonderful news. Where is she now?

239
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,230
What took you so long?

240
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,870
I didn't know about the construction
at the intersection.

241
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:50,300
I'm five minutes late. My apologies.

242
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:54,410
Shouldn't you check things like that
and plan your route ahead of time?

243
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:55,470
I apologize.

244
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:58,580
But what was so urgent
that you called for me?

245
00:13:59,140 --> 00:14:00,950
Chairman Ma's biological daughter
is alive.

246
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:04,350
What? Chairman Ma's biological daughter
is alive?

247
00:14:04,450 --> 00:14:05,550
Yes.

248
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:06,750
This is serious.

249
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:09,190
All that digging Chairman Ma
was doing for information...

250
00:14:09,590 --> 00:14:11,360
It was all for his daughter.

251
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:12,620
Her name is Ma Eun Hye.

252
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,260
And she's apparently alive.

253
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:18,800
But I heard she died in an accident
when she was just a baby.

254
00:14:18,830 --> 00:14:23,170
I heard it directly from Lee Seong Hye,
Lee Seong Sil's younger sister.

255
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:24,300
This is the real deal.

256
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:26,240
That's why Chairman Ma
has been making his moves.

257
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,140
- Then...
- First, tail Secretary Kim...

258
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,410
and see what he’s digging up.

259
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:34,880
And stop him
from investigating Ma Eun Hye any further.

260
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:37,680
And find out what Secretary Kim
has already dug up.

261
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:40,880
We have to find out about Ma Eun Hye
before they do.

262
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:41,990
Before anyone else.

263
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:44,590
- Yes, ma'am.
- There's no time.

264
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:48,060
Chairman Ma might go to the police station
to register his DNA.

265
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:52,500
What if Ma Eun Hye has already registered
and they get a match?

266
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:56,030
- We're finished.
- Yes, I'll get on it right away.

267
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:14,620
What do you want?

268
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:20,790
Oh my.
I guess my dear Kang Hyuk isn't here.

269
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,560
Your dear Kang Hyuk?

270
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:27,870
These are his clothes.
I had them cleaned for him.

271
00:15:28,130 --> 00:15:31,170
I brought his clothes over,
thinking he’d be here,

272
00:15:31,170 --> 00:15:32,400
but I guess he’s out.

273
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,110
Why do you have Manager Lee's clothes?

274
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,040
I wonder.

275
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,210
Take a guess.

276
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:42,150
Why don't you use that brilliant mind
and figure it out?

277
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,610
But then again,

278
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:45,550
I guess you're not that smart after all.

279
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:48,020
You're just good at seducing men.

280
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:51,660
- Seducing? Watch your mouth.
- Are we dropping the formalities now?

281
00:15:53,290 --> 00:15:56,590
With your trashy background,

282
00:15:57,130 --> 00:15:59,200
what else would you have learned besides
how to seduce men?

283
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,030
What did you just say?

284
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:03,000
You think you can say whatever
you want to me?

285
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:05,800
- You've really got some nerve, don't you?
- Oh dear.

286
00:16:06,370 --> 00:16:09,310
So you're saying the gloves are off?

287
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:13,680
Chae Hwa Young,

288
00:16:14,010 --> 00:16:16,450
you're thinking
you’re ready for a fresh start...

289
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,520
with Kang Nam Bong and Kang Jun Ho,

290
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:21,090
but that's not going to happen.
Want to know why?

291
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:23,590
Because before any of that can happen,

292
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,090
you'll be in jail.

293
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,360
What have you been up to
with Lee Kang Hyuk?

294
00:16:29,860 --> 00:16:33,630
Tell me. Are you two a thing now?

295
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,170
Tell me.

296
00:16:35,470 --> 00:16:38,270
I don't know what nonsense Lee Kang Hyuk
has been feeding you,

297
00:16:38,970 --> 00:16:41,610
but what is this ridiculous talk
about me going to jail?

298
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:46,410
Why would I tell you what he said?
What's in it for me?

299
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,610
Mark my words.

300
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:52,050
You stabbed me in the heart.

301
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,750
I'll pay you back a thousand times over.

302
00:16:55,990 --> 00:16:58,190
Han Young Ja, don't test me.

303
00:17:01,290 --> 00:17:02,560
You're the one who shouldn't test me.

304
00:17:03,390 --> 00:17:05,730
Hey! Darn it!

305
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:08,730
Darn it!

306
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,740
What? Chairman Ma
had a biological daughter?

307
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:18,380
Yes, but he thought she died
when she was a baby.

308
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,310
He's recently found out
that she's actually alive.

309
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:23,850
What a crazy story. He must be so happy.

310
00:17:24,150 --> 00:17:26,880
Finding out that someone
you thought was dead is actually alive...

311
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,650
It would change your whole world.

312
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,750
So she'd be your aunt, then.

313
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:32,820
So where is this aunt of yours?

314
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:36,030
He doesn't know where she is,
but he's looking for her.

315
00:17:36,130 --> 00:17:37,390
I like Grandfather.

316
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:40,500
I have to apologize to Grandfather.

317
00:17:40,630 --> 00:17:44,940
Mom, Grandfather loves soybean paste stew.
Should we go over and make some for him?

318
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:48,570
That's a great idea.
Suk Hee makes the best soybean paste stew.

319
00:17:49,570 --> 00:17:52,610
- I miss Tok Hee, too.
- Okay, Mom.

320
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:55,510
We'll go when Grandfather
and Seo Rin are free.

321
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:04,860
How's your leg?

322
00:18:05,860 --> 00:18:07,360
It seems like it's gotten a lot better.

323
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,400
Don't hide your feelings, Jang Mi.

324
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:17,330
Excuse me?

325
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,370
I'm not an idiot.

326
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,110
That night...

327
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:24,210
I know you felt something for me.

328
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,640
Don't get the wrong idea.

329
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:29,750
Actually, that was the day I became sure
of my feelings for Baek Ho.

330
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:32,780
You're just saying that so you'll feel
less guilty about Baek Ho, right?

331
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,450
Look, Kang Jun Ho.

332
00:18:37,190 --> 00:18:41,160
- What?
- Please, don't stoop so low.

333
00:18:42,390 --> 00:18:43,860
If I'm really that low,

334
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:46,260
and you find me so repulsive,

335
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:49,470
then how did you spend the whole night
in a room with me?

336
00:18:49,530 --> 00:18:52,340
Look, Kang Jun Ho, you know
it was because of the circumstances.

337
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,970
Search your heart again.

338
00:18:55,010 --> 00:18:57,540
I'm sure there's a place for me
in your heart.

339
00:18:58,310 --> 00:18:59,880
You just haven't realized it yet.

340
00:19:08,090 --> 00:19:09,120
That's ridiculous.

341
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:12,060
He's Chae Hwa Young's son, after all.

342
00:19:12,620 --> 00:19:13,720
He's so arrogant and pushy.

343
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:21,170
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

344
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:26,770
Shouldn't you at least greet
your superior?

345
00:19:28,840 --> 00:19:31,710
I've never considered you my superior.

346
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:37,450
That little punk.

347
00:19:40,450 --> 00:19:41,450
Jang Mi.

348
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:45,090
I was just about to bring you some coffee.

349
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:47,060
I figured you would, so I came to you.

350
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:50,790
Jun Ho just left. Did you run into him?

351
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:52,760
Yes, I ran into him.

352
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:00,740
Are you okay?

353
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:02,910
About what?

354
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:06,040
Because of me,
you and Jun Ho have had a falling out.

355
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:09,610
Don't worry about it.
Besides, we're not even related by blood.

356
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,680
But you were so proud of him...

357
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,550
and you looked up to him
as your older brother.

358
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:14,890
I don’t care anymore.

359
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:18,390
The brother I used to know is gone.

360
00:20:19,220 --> 00:20:23,130
Now he's just Chae Hwa Young's son
and a threat standing in my way.

361
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:27,900
But why are you letting Kang Jun Ho
off the hook?

362
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:29,700
You could have had him kicked out.

363
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:32,270
It's because of Seo Rin.

364
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:38,340
If Grandfather kicks Jun Ho out,
it’ll be even more painful for Seo Rin.

365
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,110
I guess that makes sense.

366
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:47,520
You have such a good heart, Jang Mi.

367
00:20:48,050 --> 00:20:49,490
This is why I love you.

368
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,260
Just my heart? What about my face?

369
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:53,860
Everything about you is beautiful.

370
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,800
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

371
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:04,800
Jun Ho.

372
00:21:05,370 --> 00:21:06,370
We need to talk.

373
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:08,410
If you're here to lecture me,
don't bother.

374
00:21:09,570 --> 00:21:11,140
I'm not here to nag you.

375
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,610
I want to discuss our plan moving forward.

376
00:21:15,980 --> 00:21:16,980
Plans?

377
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:19,120
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

378
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:21,490
What are you scheming now?

379
00:21:22,290 --> 00:21:24,390
I'm so sick and tired of you.

380
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:25,990
Jun Ho.

381
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:30,490
If you hadn't gotten between me
and Jang Mi,

382
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:33,660
things might have actually worked out
between me and Jang Mi.

383
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,530
The person who gave me the will to live...

384
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:38,470
and the person I love most
in this world...

385
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:41,670
Why did they have to be your enemies?

386
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,070
The one who gave you the will to live?

387
00:21:45,140 --> 00:21:46,540
Are you talking about Han Young Ja?

388
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:48,510
Jang Mi's mother.

389
00:21:49,110 --> 00:21:51,150
When I was little, at the villa,
she fed me...

390
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:53,620
and taught me to read.
She was such a kind woman.

391
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:56,920
I found out that woman was none other than
Jang Mi's mother.

392
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:58,060
What?

393
00:21:58,590 --> 00:22:00,690
You're saying you remember Jung Suk Hee?

394
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,660
That hairpin you stole
from Jang Mi's house.

395
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:06,460
I'm the one who gave it to her.

396
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:10,130
I don't know what you're talking about.

397
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:11,870
I despise you,

398
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:14,340
and I'll always despise you.

399
00:22:16,570 --> 00:22:18,180
Jun Ho.

400
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:20,710
What's wrong with him?

401
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:22,380
This is so frustrating.

402
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:26,750
Ha Neul.

403
00:22:27,420 --> 00:22:28,650
Mommy will find you.

404
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:30,990
Don't you worry. I'll find you.

405
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:34,760
I'll find you no matter what. I swear it.

406
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:45,900
So this is the oldest orphanage
in Incheon?

407
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:48,870
Yes. She was known
as the "necklace baby" there.

408
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:50,240
But when she turned three,
she was given...

409
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:52,840
the orphanage director’s surname
and named Park Young Mi.

410
00:22:53,610 --> 00:22:56,180
Then it should be easy to find her, right?

411
00:22:56,350 --> 00:22:58,150
The orphanage became overcrowded,

412
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:01,050
so she was transferred to one
in Pyeongtaek.

413
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:05,760
But about 40 years ago,
the records were lost in a flood.

414
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:07,620
So...

415
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:11,290
Is my Eun Hye living as Park Young Mi?

416
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:14,530
Most likely, for administrative purposes,
the new orphanage...

417
00:23:15,030 --> 00:23:17,800
formally registered her under a new name.

418
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:21,000
So we can't even be sure of her name.

419
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:23,110
Oh, no.

420
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:25,840
What about that scumbag broker?

421
00:23:26,310 --> 00:23:29,580
- Are you still looking for him?
- Yes, I am,

422
00:23:30,010 --> 00:23:31,750
but I don't have many leads yet.

423
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:34,420
All right. Good work.

424
00:23:38,890 --> 00:23:42,060
So much time has passed,
and she'd be over 50 by now.

425
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:43,960
Wait a minute...

426
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,400
What if, like Seong Hye said,
my Eun Hye...

427
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:51,070
registered her DNA a long time ago?

428
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:55,070
I'd better do it right away.

429
00:23:58,010 --> 00:24:02,150
Hey. Get the car ready.
I need to go to the police station.

430
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,060
Hong Ju!

431
00:24:18,330 --> 00:24:19,700
What's going on, Mom?

432
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,570
I think the Chairman is about
to find his real daughter.

433
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:26,870
The day they reunite, we'll be finished.
What are we going to do?

434
00:24:26,870 --> 00:24:29,970
I don't know! How can we stop
the Chairman from finding his daughter?

435
00:24:30,040 --> 00:24:33,840
The Chairman went to the police station
to register his DNA.

436
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:37,410
What? He went to the police station
to register his DNA?

437
00:24:37,980 --> 00:24:41,250
- Oh my gosh!
- My grandfather went to register his DNA?

438
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:45,660
That's great. I hope he finds her soon.

439
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:59,600
Chairman Ma is going to the police station
to register his DNA.

440
00:25:00,140 --> 00:25:02,810
What? That old bastard.

441
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:09,280
How could you mess up this badly?
I told you to keep a close tail on him,

442
00:25:09,650 --> 00:25:11,080
so what happens if he registers his DNA...

443
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:13,750
and Ma Eun Hye
has already registered hers?

444
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:16,250
It'll only be a matter of time
before they're reunited.

445
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:19,420
I only knew he went to the police station
because I was tailing him.

446
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:23,060
How was I supposed to stop him,
especially when it's the Chairman himself?

447
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:27,430
And you're proud of that?
Lee Kang Hyuk, what are you up to?

448
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:30,100
What did you do to Han Young Ja
to make her bring this here?

449
00:25:30,770 --> 00:25:34,670
- Did she bring this?
- Lee Kang Hyuk.

450
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:38,410
Don't tell me you're planning
to betray me.

451
00:25:39,210 --> 00:25:41,580
If you betray me,

452
00:25:42,210 --> 00:25:45,750
you're going down with me.
Just remember that.

453
00:25:55,690 --> 00:25:56,690
Yes, Ms. Ma.

454
00:25:57,760 --> 00:25:59,760
It's me, Chae Hwa Young,
Chairman Ma's daughter-in-law.

455
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,100
A necklace?

456
00:26:04,330 --> 00:26:07,540
Dae Chang gave my sister a necklace
to comfort her...

457
00:26:07,540 --> 00:26:09,340
during a difficult time.

458
00:26:09,810 --> 00:26:12,680
And my sister apparently gave it
to Eun Hye.

459
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:16,880
I heard that from the housekeeper,
but I forgot to tell you.

460
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:21,150
You're the CEO of the hotel,
so you must be well-connected.

461
00:26:21,620 --> 00:26:25,160
We need all the help we can get
to find our Eun Hye quickly.

462
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:30,190
So, Ma Eun Hye
might still have the necklace.

463
00:26:30,330 --> 00:26:32,100
I hope she does,

464
00:26:32,660 --> 00:26:35,630
but it's been so long.
I'm not sure if she still keeps it.

465
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:41,100
And did my mother-in-law...

466
00:26:41,540 --> 00:26:43,510
do the four-leaf clover embroidery?

467
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:47,610
Of course.
My sister was very good with her hands.

468
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:50,410
She believed four-leaf clovers
brought good luck.

469
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:53,280
She embroidered them on Eun Hye's clothes,
her bibs,

470
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:57,990
and even her husband's handkerchiefs.

471
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:00,590
I see.

472
00:27:24,380 --> 00:27:27,050
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

473
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:32,460
What?

474
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:35,230
The thief is here!

475
00:27:36,890 --> 00:27:37,930
Is anyone else here?

476
00:27:39,460 --> 00:27:40,560
Suk Hee is here.

477
00:27:48,170 --> 00:27:51,540
I haven't seen that necklace before.
Where did you get it?

478
00:27:53,010 --> 00:27:55,750
Go away, you thief!
This necklace is Suk Hee's.

479
00:27:56,050 --> 00:27:57,680
Get out of here now, you thief!

480
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,380
(The First Man)

481
00:28:29,610 --> 00:28:31,650
I'm only part
of your professional life, ma'am,

482
00:28:31,650 --> 00:28:33,120
not your personal life.

483
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:36,290
So, are you saying Lawyer Han
is part of your personal life?

484
00:28:36,750 --> 00:28:40,190
So, Chae Hwa Young must also know
the Chairman's daughter is alive.

485
00:28:40,620 --> 00:28:41,720
What are you talking about?

486
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:45,060
So, Chae Hwa Young knows my aunt is alive.

487
00:28:45,730 --> 00:28:48,330
There has to be more information
on Ma Eun Hye somewhere.

488
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:51,530
Mom, what are you doing here?

489
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,000
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
